  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "tigervnc security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for tigervnc is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP2,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This package provides client for Virtual Network Computing (VNC), with which you can access any other desktops running a VNC server.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nIn TigerVNC before 1.16.2, Image.cxx in x0vncserver allows other users to observe or manipulate the screen contents, or cause an application crash, because of incorrect permissions.(CVE-2026-34352)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for tigervnc is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP2,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of high. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "High",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "tigervnc",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
